  "local_port": 50730,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "Using WhatsApp on a PC can be done in a couple of ways: through the WhatsApp Web interface or by installing the WhatsApp Desktop application. Here\u2019s how to do both:\n\n### Method 1: WhatsApp Web\n\n1. **Open a Web Browser**: Go to [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com).\n\n2. **Link Your Phone**:\n    - Open WhatsApp on your smartphone.\n    - For Android: Tap the three dots in the top right corner and select \"WhatsApp Web\". For iPhone: Go to \"Settings\" and tap \"Linked Devices\".\n    - Use your phone to scan the QR code that appears on the browser.\n\n3. **Start Chatting**: Once the QR code is scanned successfully, your chats will be mirrored on the web browser, and you can start sending and receiving messages.\n\n4. **Stay Connected**: Ensure your phone stays connected to the internet while using WhatsApp Web.\n\n### Method 2: WhatsApp Desktop Application\n\n1. **Download the Application**:\n    - Go to the official WhatsApp website at [whatsapp.com/download](https://www.whatsapp.com/download).\n    - Download the desktop app for Windows or Mac depending on your operating system.\n\n2. **Install the Application**: Open the downloaded file and follow the installation instructions.\n\n3. **Link Your Phone**:\n    - Open the WhatsApp desktop application.\n    - Similar to WhatsApp Web, open WhatsApp on your phone.\n    - For Android: Tap the three dots in the top right corner and select \"WhatsApp Web\". For iPhone: Go to \"Settings\" and tap \"Linked Devices\".\n    - Scan the QR code displayed on your desktop application with your phone.\n\n4. **Start Chatting**: Once the QR code is scanned, you can use WhatsApp directly from your desktop.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Notifications**: You can enable desktop notifications to stay updated about incoming messages.\n- **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Familiarize yourself with keyboard shortcuts to enhance your experience.\n- **Multi-Device Support**: Check if your WhatsApp version supports linked devices. This feature allows you to use WhatsApp on the PC without needing your phone connected.\n\nNow you're ready to use WhatsApp on your PC!",
